openmediavault-themekit (1.0.7) stable; urgency=medium

  * Replaced background `exec(omv-salt ...)` call in the RPC `set` method with a proper omv-engined module listener following the standard OpenMediaVault plugin architecture.
  * Added `engined/module/themekit.inc` implementing `ServiceAbstract` and `IListener`, which marks the module dirty via `setDirty()` on configuration changes.
  * CSS is now only regenerated when the user explicitly clicks Apply Changes, consistent with how all other OMV plugins behave.
  * Optimized RPC `set` method: cache `getAssoc()` result once and reuse it for both `notify()` and the return value instead of calling it three times.
  * Fixed variable name collision in `download_font.py`: inner binary download variable `font_data` renamed to `font_binary` to avoid shadowing the outer DB lookup variable.
  * Added `| string` filter to `user-custom.css.j2` to prevent Jinja re-evaluation of user-provided CSS content containing `{{ }}` syntax.
  * Added log rotation to `download_font.py`: log file is rotated at 500 KB to prevent unbounded growth.
  * Added explicit `return` after `finish()` calls at early-exit points in `download_font.py` to make control flow unambiguous.
  * Fixed formatting in `postinst` and `postrm` scripts.
  * Updated `debian/control` description to mention typography and custom CSS features; fixed line wrapping per Debian policy.

 -- Saurabh Nakkarike <gradelabsin@gmail.com>  Tue, 15 Jul 2026 19:46:00 +0530

openmediavault-themekit (1.0.6) stable; urgency=medium

  * SECURITY: Fixed YAML/Jinja injection vulnerability in Salt states by enforcing JSON serialization (`| json`) for all dynamically injected variables.
  * Fixed persistent 404 error for `theme-font.css` by correctly generating a blank stylesheet when no font is selected or custom typography is disabled.
  * Cleaned up backend RPC by establishing the XML database as the sole source of truth, dropping heavy fallback reads and `syslog()` debug dumps.
  * Added missing schema toggles (`enableTypography` and `enableCustomCss`) to the `confdb` seed script to prevent validation errors on initial plugin load.
  * Removed legacy `xmlstarlet` dependencies from the `postinst` upgrade script to improve reliability on modern OMV versions.
  * SECURITY: Fixed potential CSS injection vulnerability by escaping single and double quotes in custom font names via Jinja before rendering.
  * Fixed performance issue by implementing MD5 hash-based cache-busting for CSS injection in index.html, allowing the browser to cache files when unchanged.
  * Fixed unconditional execution of the font download Salt state by implementing a proper stateful python script that accurately reports changes.
  * Fixed missing datamodel validation for RPC requests by adding a dedicated `rpc.themekit.set` JSON schema and enforcing strict server-side validation on incoming API payloads.
  * Fixed race conditions causing `index.html` corruption by implementing an exclusive `flock` lock around the background Salt state deployments.
  * Improved upgrade reliability by removing unconditional `nginx` and `php-fpm` reloads from the `postinst` script, preventing unnecessary web server restarts.

 -- Saurabh Nakkarike <gradelabsin@gmail.com>  Wed, 15 Jul 2026 16:35:00 +0530

